22/12/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- In separate statements Thursday (December 21st), Christina Gallach, spokesperson for EU security chief Javier Solana, and US Deputy Assistant Secretary of State Rosemary DiCarlo urged Albania's parties to reach a compromise regarding upcoming local elections. 
Gallach noted Albania is still in a transitional period and does not need such political conflict. 
DiCarlo said holding free and fair elections is key to Albania's integration future. 
She urged political leaders to sit down together and overcome their differences. 
(Albanian News - 22/12/06)
